{
  "texts": [
    "For example, with g = 4, 6 pairs are obtained from one forward pass instead of 6 forward passes.",
    "These two mechanisms together reduce both the number of pairs processed and the cost per pair, resulting in 1.7-5.4× faster convergence in our experiments.",
    "As datasets grow, the number of redundant pairs increases, but clustering should discard them.",
    "Consequently, the relative efficiency gain of g-DPO compounds with dataset size and with the structure of the underlying mutational landscape.",
    "pairs and is therefore more sensitive to local ordering differences."
  ]
}